---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="5 Must have Shopify apps for new stores"
  description="Discover the best Shopify apps every new store owner needs to succeed, from email marketing to customer reviews and beyond."
>
  <main class="space-y-20 px-5">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl py-8 lg:py-16">
      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <nav class="mb-8 flex items-center space-x-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
        <a href="/help" class="hover:text-[#6d28d9]">Help Center</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span class="text-gray-900">5 Must have Shopify apps</span>
      </nav>

      <!-- Article Header -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <div class="mb-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-[#6d28d9]/10 px-4 py-1">
          <span class="text-sm font-medium text-[#6d28d9]">Getting Started</span
          >
        </div>
        <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl leading-tight font-bold md:text-5xl">
          5 Must have Shopify apps for new stores
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
          Starting a new Shopify store? These essential apps will help you grow
          your business, increase conversions, and provide an exceptional
          customer experience from day one.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Article Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <h2 class="mt-8 mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">Why These Apps Matter</h2>
        <p>
          When you're launching a new Shopify store, choosing the right apps
          can make the difference between struggling and thriving. The apps
          we've selected below are battle-tested essentials that address the
          core needs of any e-commerce business: marketing, social proof,
          conversions, and customer support.
        </p>

        <!-- App 1: Klaviyo -->
        <div class="my-8 rounded-xl border-2 border-[#6d28d9]/20 bg-white p-8">
          <div class="mb-4 flex items-start justify-between">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#6d28d9]">1. Klaviyo</h2>
          </div>

          <p class="mb-4 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">
            The Gold Standard for E-commerce Email Marketing
          </p>

          <p>
            Klaviyo is hands down the most powerful email marketing platform
            for Shopify stores. Unlike generic email tools, Klaviyo is built
            specifically for e-commerce, with deep integration into your store's
            data.
          </p>

          <h3 class="mt-6 mb-3 text-xl font-semibold">Why You Need It:</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
            <li>
              <strong>Automated Flows:</strong> Set up abandoned cart emails, welcome
              series, post purchase follow ups, and win back campaigns that run on
              autopilot
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Advanced Segmentation:</strong> Target customers based on their
              behavior, purchase history, and engagement level
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Revenue Attribution:</strong> See exactly how much money each
              email campaign generates
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>SMS Marketing:</strong> Combine email and SMS for maximum reach
            </li>
          </ul>

          <div
            class="mt-6 rounded-lg border border-green-200 bg-green-50 p-4"
          >
            <p class="text-sm text-green-900">
              <strong>ðŸ’¡ Pro Tip:</strong> Start with the basic flows first - abandoned
              cart and welcome series can generate 20-30% of your email revenue with
              minimal effort.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-6">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              <strong>Pricing:</strong> Free up to 250 contacts, then starts at $20/month
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- App 2: Judge.me -->
        <div class="my-8 rounded-xl border-2 border-[#6d28d9]/20 bg-white p-8">
          <div class="mb-4 flex items-start justify-between">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#6d28d9]">2. Judge.me</h2>
          </div>

          <p class="mb-4 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">
            Build Trust with Authentic Customer Reviews
          </p>

          <p>
            Social proof is critical for new stores. Judge.me makes it easy to
            collect and display customer reviews, helping you build credibility
            even when you're just starting out.
          </p>

          <h3 class="mt-6 mb-3 text-xl font-semibold">Why You Need It:</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
            <li>
              <strong>Automated Review Requests:</strong> Automatically send review
              request emails after purchase
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Photo & Video Reviews:</strong> Let customers upload images
              and videos of your products in action
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Rich Snippets:</strong> Display star ratings in Google search
              results to increase click-through rates
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Easy Import:</strong> Import reviews from other platforms or
              previous stores
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Unlimited Reviews:</strong> No limits on the number of reviews
              you can collect, even on free plan
            </li>
          </ul>

          <div
            class="mt-6 rounded-lg border border-green-200 bg-green-50 p-4"
          >
            <p class="text-sm text-green-900">
              <strong>ðŸ’¡ Pro Tip:</strong> Offer a small incentive (like a discount
              code) for customers who leave reviews to kickstart your review collection.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-6">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              <strong>Pricing:</strong> Free plan available, premium plans start
              at $15/month
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- App 3: Privy -->
        <div class="my-8 rounded-xl border-2 border-[#6d28d9]/20 bg-white p-8">
          <div class="mb-4 flex items-start justify-between">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#6d28d9]">3. Privy</h2>
          </div>

          <p class="mb-4 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">
            Grow Your Email List with Smart Popups
          </p>

          <p>
            Your email list is one of your most valuable assets. Privy helps you
            capture visitor emails with targeted popups, banners, and flyouts
            that actually convert.
          </p>

          <h3 class="mt-6 mb-3 text-xl font-semibold">Why You Need It:</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
            <li>
              <strong>Exit-Intent Popups:</strong> Capture visitors right before
              they leave your site
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Spin-to-Win Wheels:</strong> Gamify the signup process to
              increase engagement
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Cart Abandonment Emails:</strong> Recover lost sales with automated
              follow-ups (if not using Klaviyo's version)
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>A/B Testing:</strong> Test different offers and designs to
              optimize conversion rates
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Mobile Optimized:</strong> All displays are designed to work
              perfectly on mobile devices
            </li>
          </ul>

          <div
            class="mt-6 rounded-lg border border-green-200 bg-green-50 p-4"
          >
            <p class="text-sm text-green-900">
              <strong>ðŸ’¡ Pro Tip:</strong> Offer a compelling first-purchase discount
              (10-15% off) to new email subscribers. This grows your list AND drives
              immediate sales.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-6">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              <strong>Pricing:</strong> Free up to 100 mailable contacts, paid plans
              start at $30/month
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- App 4: ReConvert -->
        <div class="my-8 rounded-xl border-2 border-[#6d28d9]/20 bg-white p-8">
          <div class="mb-4 flex items-start justify-between">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#6d28d9]">4. ReConvert</h2>
          </div>

          <p class="mb-4 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">
            Maximize Order Value with Post Purchase Offers
          </p>

          <p>
            Your thank you page is prime real estate that most stores waste.
            ReConvert transforms it into a revenue generating machine with
            one click upsells and cross sells.
          </p>

          <h3 class="mt-6 mb-3 text-xl font-semibold">Why You Need It:</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
            <li>
              <strong>One Click Upsells:</strong> Customers can add products to
              their order without re-entering payment info
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Thank You Page Builder:</strong> Customize your thank you
              page with upsells, surveys, and social proof
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Birthday Collector:</strong> Gather customer birthdays for
              future marketing campaigns
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Post Purchase Surveys:</strong> Learn how customers found
              your store to optimize marketing spend
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Checkout Page Widgets:</strong> Add trust badges and urgency
              timers to increase conversions
            </li>
          </ul>

          <div
            class="mt-6 rounded-lg border border-green-200 bg-green-50 p-4"
          >
            <p class="text-sm text-green-900">
              <strong>ðŸ’¡ Pro Tip:</strong> Start with complementary products at a
              lower price point than the original purchase. Customers are in a buying
              mood and more likely to add on.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-6">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              <strong>Pricing:</strong> Free plan available, paid plans start at
              $7.99/month
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- App 5: PageFly -->
        <div class="my-8 rounded-xl border-2 border-[#6d28d9]/20 bg-white p-8">
          <div class="mb-4 flex items-start justify-between">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#6d28d9]">5. PageFly</h2>
          </div>

          <p class="mb-4 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">
            Create Stunning Landing Pages Without Code
          </p>

          <p>
            Your store's design can make or break conversions. PageFly gives you
            the power to create beautiful, high converting landing pages,
            product pages, and homepages without touching a line of code.
          </p>

          <h3 class="mt-6 mb-3 text-xl font-semibold">Why You Need It:</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
            <li>
              <strong>Drag-and-Drop Builder:</strong> Intuitive visual editor that
              anyone can use
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Mobile-First Design:</strong> All pages are automatically optimized
              for mobile devices
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Pre-Built Templates:</strong> 100+ professionally designed
              templates to start from
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Section Library:</strong> Save and reuse sections across different
              pages
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Lightning Fast:</strong> Optimized code ensures your pages
              load quickly for better SEO
            </li>
          </ul>

          <div
            class="mt-6 rounded-lg border border-green-200 bg-green-50 p-4"
          >
            <p class="text-sm text-green-900">
              <strong>ðŸ’¡ Pro Tip:</strong> Create dedicated landing pages for your
              paid ads instead of sending traffic to your homepage. You'll see significantly
              better conversion rates.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-6">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              <strong>Pricing:</strong> Free plan available with 1 published page,
              paid plans start at $24/month
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Bonus: EasyEdit Plug -->
        <div
          class="my-12 rounded-xl border-2 border-[#6d28d9] bg-gradient-to-br from-[#6d28d9]/5 to-[#6d28d9]/10 p-8"
        >
          <div class="mb-6 text-center">
            <span
              class="inline-block rounded-full bg-[#6d28d9] px-4 py-2 text-sm font-bold text-white"
            >
              BONUS APP
            </span>
          </div>

          <h2 class="mb-4 text-center text-3xl font-bold text-[#6d28d9]">
            EasyEdit - Order Editing
          </h2>

          <p class="mb-4 text-center text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">
            Reduce support tickets by up to 90%
          </p>

          <p class="mb-6">
            While the five apps above are essential for growth, there's one more
            app that will save you countless hours and dramatically improve
            customer satisfaction: <strong>EasyEdit</strong>.
          </p>

          <p class="mb-6">
            Nothing kills momentum faster than drowning in customer support
            tickets asking to modify orders. "Can I change my address?" "I
            ordered the wrong size." "I want to add another item." These simple
            requests can consume hours of your day.
          </p>

          <h3 class="mt-6 mb-3 text-xl font-semibold">
            How EasyEdit Transforms Your Support Operations:
          </h3>
          <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
            <li>
              <strong>Empower Your Customers:</strong> Let customers edit their
              own orders - change addresses, swap products, update quantities, or
              cancel - all without contacting support
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Reduce Support Tickets:</strong> Stores using EasyEdit report
              up to 90% reduction in order related support tickets
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Increase Customer Satisfaction:</strong> Customers get instant
              resolution instead of waiting hours (or days) for support responses
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Save Time & Money:</strong> Free up your support team to focus
              on complex issues that actually need human attention
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Boost Revenue:</strong> Customers can add items to their orders,
              increasing average order value
            </li>
          </ul>

          <div
            class="mt-6 rounded-lg border border-[#6d28d9]/30 bg-white p-4"
          >
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-900">
              <strong>ðŸš€ Real Results:</strong> New store owners consistently report
              that EasyEdit is one of the best investments they made. Instead of
              spending your first months glued to support tickets, you can focus
              on marketing, product development, and growing your business.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-8 text-center">
            <a
              href="https://apps.shopify.com/easyedit-order-editing"
              class="inline-flex rounded-xl bg-[#6d28d9] px-8 py-4 text-lg font-semibold text-white shadow-lg duration-200 hover:scale-105 hover:bg-[#5a1fb8] hover:shadow-xl"
            >
              Start 30-Day Free Trial
            </a>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-600">
              Setup in 2 minutes
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">
          Getting Started with These Apps
        </h2>
        <p>
          You don't need to install all of these apps on day one. Here's a
          recommended priority order:
        </p>

        <ol class="mt-6 list-decimal space-y-3 pl-6">
          <li>
            <strong>Start with Klaviyo</strong> - Get your email marketing infrastructure
            in place first. Set up basic flows before you even launch.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Add Judge.me immediately</strong> - Even if you have no reviews
            yet, having the system in place means you'll start collecting them from
            your first sales.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Install EasyEdit before launch</strong> - Don't wait until
            you're drowning in support tickets. Set it up from day one.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Set up Privy within the first week</strong> - Start building
            your email list as soon as you have traffic.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Add ReConvert and PageFly when needed</strong> - These are powerful
            optimization tools, but you can add them once you have some baseline
            traffic and sales.
          </li>
        </ol>

        <div
          class="my-8 rounded-xl border border-[#6d28d9]/20 bg-[#6d28d9]/5 p-6"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start">
            <svg
              class="mt-1 mr-3 h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 text-[#6d28d9]"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
            <div>
              <h3 class="mb-2 font-semibold text-[#6d28d9]">
                Important Note on App Costs
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                While apps cost money, they're investments that pay for
                themselves many times over. A store earning $10,000/month can
                easily justify $200-300/month in apps if they're driving growth
                and saving time. Start with free plans and upgrade as you grow.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">Final Thoughts</h2>
        <p>
          Building a successful Shopify store isn't just about having great
          products - it's about having the right tools to market them, build
          trust, and provide excellent customer experiences. These five apps
          (plus EasyEdit!) form the foundation of a professional, scalable
          e-commerce operation.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-4">
          Remember: the best app stack is one that you'll actually use. Start
          simple, master each tool, and add more as your business grows. Your
          future self will thank you for setting up these systems early.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Contact Support CTA -->
      <div class="rounded-base mt-16 bg-[#6d28d9]/5 p-8 text-center">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold">Questions about EasyEdit?</h2>
        <p class="mb-6 text-gray-600">
          Want to learn more about how EasyEdit can reduce your support load
          and improve customer satisfaction? We're here to help.
        </p>
        <div
          class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 sm:flex-row"
        >
          <a
            href="/#contact"
            class="flex w-64 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-[#6d28d9] px-8 py-4 text-lg font-normal text-white shadow-lg duration-200 hover:scale-105 hover:bg-[#5a1fb8] hover:shadow-xl"
          >
            Contact Us
          </a>
          <a
            href="/help"
            class="flex w-64 items-center justify-center rounded-xl border border-gray-300 bg-white px-8 py-4 text-lg font-normal text-gray-900 shadow-sm duration-200 hover:scale-105 hover:shadow-md"
          >
            Back to Help Center
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</MainLayout>
